The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of non-uniform vote aggregation, which involves processing and analyzing data. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Additionally, the paper proposes two different aggregation methods, which involve machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses distance measures and Markov chains, which are topics related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Statistical Learning (cs.SI), respectively.
